org.openimaj.util.function.context

Class ContextListFunction<IN,OUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.util.function.context.ContextAdaptor<Function<IN,OUT>,List<IN>,List<OUT>>
      • org.openimaj.util.function.context.ContextListFunction<IN,OUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    IN - The input type of the function (and the type of elements in the list)
    OUT - The output type of the function (and type of elements in the resultant list)
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Function<Context,Context>

    public class ContextListFunction<IN,OUT>
extends ContextAdaptor<Function<IN,OUT>,List<IN>,List<OUT>>
implements Function<Context,Context>
    Apply a Function to a list held within a single element of a Context, writing the resultant list back to the Context, potentially with a different key.
    Author:
    Sina Samangooei (ss@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
